      "title": "The Right to Receive Information",
      "abstract": "Ms. Mart examines the legal evolution of the right to receive information, particularly ::: focusing on its application to libraries, beginning with the Supreme ::: Court holding in Board of Education v. Pico, and followed by cases that have ::: considered the meaning of Pico in a variety of library-related contexts."
